<subSubSection id="54EB17E9FF87640BFF689D31FCBEFCE4" pageId="13" pageNumber="530" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1C4E4462FF87640BFF689D31FCBEFCE4" blockId="13.[151,1436,438,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis id="2E859870FF87640BFF689D31FE94FCAD" bold="true" box="[199,331,798,823]" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Etymology</emphasis>
Name formed by combining the suffix 
<emphasis id="2E859870FF87640BFC879D31FCA7FCAD" box="[808,888,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Berber</emphasis>
(pertaining to the Maghrebian Roman region, Barbaria, and the prevailing ethnic group in northern Maghreb) and the prefix –getta, an arbitrary combination of letters associated with small cicada species, as in 
<taxonomicName id="DBF13FE1FF87640BFD409D48FC84FCE4" box="[751,859,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tettigetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2E859870FF87640BFD409D48FC84FCE4" box="[751,859,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Tettigetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
